06:09.661 --> 06:10.823
Okay, good morning, everyone.

06:10.883 --> 06:12.807
Ben Selya, senior performance analyst.

06:13.167 --> 06:14.790
I'll give you a brief introduction here.

06:14.910 --> 06:24.127
I'll cover the survey purpose, the administration, the survey structure, as well as a brief snapshot of the response rate in the participation this year.

06:25.128 --> 06:26.050
Next slide, please.

06:27.785 --> 06:36.498
The primary purpose of the employee survey as it relates to the board is it helps us populate the metrics for the agency performance scorecard.

06:36.538 --> 06:40.665
So that's probably where you're most familiar with the data that comes out of this survey.

06:40.745 --> 06:46.593
As you can see, all the metrics in this example here come straight out of the employee survey.

06:46.614 --> 06:47.895
So that's where we get that data.

06:48.917 --> 06:52.943
The survey also helps us collect direct employee feedback.

06:53.244 --> 06:56.188
We do that through not only the text field, but also

06:56.489 --> 06:59.575
through the multiple choice questions.

07:00.257 --> 07:03.463
And it also gives us an understanding of employee satisfaction and engagement.

07:03.523 --> 07:07.912
So as you'll see in the next couple of slides, we have some questions directly aimed at that.

07:07.952 --> 07:12.000
It also provides us an opportunity for

07:12.183 --> 07:15.348
insight into areas that may need some extra attention.

07:15.828 --> 07:22.879
That happens a lot through the free text field where employees are invited to basically free text responses to us.

07:23.199 --> 07:26.324
And we actually glean a lot of information out of that text box.

07:27.225 --> 07:27.986
Next slide, please.

07:29.108 --> 07:32.313
The administration happens over a four week survey period.

07:32.333 --> 07:35.457
This year it went from April 15th through May 16th.

07:36.319 --> 07:40.705
We expanded it one year, one week from last year to four weeks.

07:41.309 --> 07:46.116
Like John said earlier, we did 16 in-person events at nine different facilities.

07:47.217 --> 07:55.089
We aim the in-person events primarily at the operational facilities where we have employees who do not spend a lot of time in front of a computer.

07:55.149 --> 07:59.655
So that helps us get the survey in front of them and get their voice into the survey.

08:01.120 --> 08:04.507
We have a number of different methods that, yeah, let's roll back.

08:04.908 --> 08:07.153
We have a number of different methods that we're currently using.

08:07.754 --> 08:10.900
At the in-person events, we use a tablet as well as the printed survey.

08:10.940 --> 08:14.648
We have employees who refer one over the other, so we allow both.

08:15.510 --> 08:16.833
It's also done online.

08:17.494 --> 08:18.957
We promote that through the hub.

08:19.298 --> 08:21.863
We also include it in the hot sheet each week.

08:22.282 --> 08:31.656
And we also push an icon to the desktops in the break rooms for operational personnel so they can simply click on an icon and take the survey online.

08:32.818 --> 08:34.981
And finally, we also do printed copies.

08:36.123 --> 08:43.134
We have a stack of copies that are just left in the break room and they can put those into a collection box at their leisure.

08:44.135 --> 08:44.796
Next slide.

08:46.953 --> 08:49.877
The survey structure remains the same as it was last year.

08:49.897 --> 08:59.430
We have five job related questions that helps us parse out the information so we can tell how things are going at various locations, departments and divisions.

09:00.271 --> 09:04.316
We also ask the likeliness of recommendation as an employer.

09:04.617 --> 09:07.020
That's where we get the net promoter score data from.

09:07.827 --> 09:10.991
We also ask about 11 internal services.

09:11.092 --> 09:15.978
So essentially we ask employees how satisfied they are with, say, IT department.

09:15.998 --> 09:17.140
And then we collect that.

09:19.684 --> 09:21.807
So ask a number of favorability questions.

09:21.827 --> 09:26.173
And that's primarily where the information from the agency scorecard comes from.

09:26.593 --> 09:31.921
Questions such as, does your supervisor treat you with respect?

09:32.121 --> 09:33.203
It's those kind of questions.

09:34.004 --> 09:37.108
And then we also have a retention-related question where we have

09:37.578 --> 09:45.045
10 items and we ask the employees to rank them from one to 10 on how important they are for keeping them here as an employee at RTD.

09:45.805 --> 09:51.030
And then finally, we have the open-ended question where they're allowed to free text, whatever they want to tell us.

09:52.251 --> 09:52.671
Next slide.

09:52.711 --> 09:58.476
Here is a brief overview of the survey of the last three years.

09:58.837 --> 10:03.781
So we're at about 32% participation this year down a little bit from last year.

10:03.841 --> 10:06.083
We still have

10:06.248 --> 10:08.571
Pretty good use of the paper survey options.

10:08.591 --> 10:12.755
So about 18% this year chose to use the paper survey over digital.

10:14.818 --> 10:19.443
