11:16.460 --> 11:20.704
So while a large percentage is non supervisory,

11:20.971 --> 11:26.158
The upshot of that is we are still getting very good voice from our frontline staff.

11:28.201 --> 11:31.927
Okay.

11:31.947 --> 11:34.690
Good morning, Jake Sudemeyer, Manager of Market Research.

11:35.171 --> 11:37.895
I'll go through the employee net promoter score.

11:38.195 --> 11:49.932
Again, a quick reminder, if you're not familiar with NPS and how it's calculated, when asking employees how likely they are to recommend working RTV friends or family, anyone answering as a nine or 10,

11:50.317 --> 11:52.540
is classified as a promoter.

11:52.900 --> 11:58.608
Any one seven or eight is a passive and then zero through six are considered detractors.

11:58.648 --> 12:06.659
So the score is calculated by just subtracting the percentage of detractors from the promoters gives us our NPS score.

12:06.679 --> 12:12.507
So as you can see in 2024 our NPS was at negative two and this year we are at four.

12:12.787 --> 12:14.009
So we've got an improvement there.

12:15.051 --> 12:16.172
Next slide please.

12:18.498 --> 12:22.727
And again, this shows you the actual percentages of those classifications.

12:22.747 --> 12:30.283
So you can see you take the 35% for promoters, subtract the 31% from the trackers, and gives our overall NPS of four.

12:31.265 --> 12:31.866
Next slide.

12:32.825 --> 12:38.391
All right, for our composite index score, going through the employee ownership composite index score.

12:38.672 --> 12:54.630
